<p><strong>Elder law</strong> encompasses the legal issues that affect older adults, including Medicaid planning, asset protection, guardianship, and long-term care planning. In Pennsylvania, Medicaid eligibility for long-term care is governed by the Department of Human Services and requires careful planning to protect assets while qualifying for benefits. Our attorneys help families navigate these complex rules with clarity and compassion.</p>
